reviews.text: One of the best vegetarian restaurants in Hong Kong. The food is delicious. The service is impeccable. Wonderful ambience. A must for all vegetarians visiting HK.
Had pad Thai and it was way too salty.  Spring rolls were okay.  Too expensive.  Best part was the service.
foods look really real and so tasty. suitable for ppl who look for vegetarian food. Staff there are nice. but unfortunately the price is a bit higher.
Good food! Friendly staff. The eggplant on the noodles was awesome. (I forgot the name of the noodles we ordered)

It's a traditional vegetarian restaurant locates at an old commercial building.  The decoration of the restaurant is simple.  The area is not small.  However, all the dishes we ordered were quite salty, even if the snacks served before the main dishes.  There was too much sticky sauce left on the plate of the dishes and they were quite oily too.  We were disappointed with the fried rice with preserved olive leaves as the preserved olive leaves were not mashed and fried evenly with the rice.

result.name: 喬妃齋

reviews.text: One of the best vegetarian restaurants in Hong Kong. The food is delicious. The service is impeccable. Wonderful ambience. A must for all vegetarians visiting HK.

喜歡這裡的阿姨和廚師都很親切
來吃了很多次，不管什麼都好吃
環境清靜,食物味道可好,多年前曾光顧過,裝修比以前優雅,食物都保持一貫水準。
Had pad Thai and it was way too salty.  Spring rolls were okay.  Too expensive.  Best part was the service.
餐點的份量多很美味，值得推薦。
